rComments: Best Prof I have had so far and I'm in fourth year. Unfortunetely he retires soon.

Amazing Prof! Absolutely loved this class! No textbook needed, all you need to do is go to class, & pay attention because he gives pop quizzes. Midterm and exam question are given before hand. I Recommend this course :)

Fantastic prof! Knows the material extremely well and makes the class super interesting. Great sense of humour and provides book recommendations which I loved! GO TO CLASS and pay attention = easy A. Low workload and no textbook to purchase. He also provides the questions to the midterm + exam before so you can prepare your answer. Take this class!

Attendance is mandatory, random quizzes worth 40% of grade. A lot of writting and nothing is posted online. The quizzes are easy if you pay attention but he marks the midterm and final really hard since he gives you the questions beforehand.
amazing professor! doesn't use a textbook. easy 10 questions quizes every now and then. very easy midterm and final. I highly recommend attending the lecture, for taking notes and the quizes.

This class was brilliant. I took ESP1101 and enjoyed, so I decided to take this class. The readings we entertaining, and I love how he accompanied the stories with their historical origins. Basically we are reading hispanic literature and doing literary analysis. Class consists of pop quizzes, a midterm, and a final. Very easy if you actually read.

One of the best profs I have had at Ottawa U, extremely dry sense of humour. Very passionate teacher. Class is organized, in order to do well you should attend every lecture to help with your essay questions. Favourite class so far!

This prof is amazing! He has all the magic in the world when he's talking about his subject. This class is also amazing, it's rare that I'm actually excited to go to class, but this one I don't mind one bit !

Very passionate about his subjects! A professor who likes to give you more details than necessary, but wants you to know concepts rather than details. You have to actually go to class and do the readings to do well as most of the marks are based on pop-quizzes but he makes it clear what you need to know.
Interesting class! It shows when a prof is passionate about what they're teaching. Readings were (relatively) short, pop quizzes every now and again but they're easy when you attend class.

This class is so interesting! Attendance is mandatory (weekly pop quizzes worth 40%) but the prof is passionate and knowledgeable about the subject. Uses Powerpoints and videos. Readings are short and posted on Virtual Campus. Hands out exam questions before the test so you can prepare! Take the class - you won't be bored :)

Quizzes (worth 40% of total mark) essentially make the class mandatory, but I loved going -- he is obviously passionate about the subject and teaches it well! If you go to class and pay attention, you should ace this course!
Very interesting class. He uses powerpoint presentations, the readings are all posted online, he plays videos in class. Overall a great class! I reccommend!

I very much enjoyed this class! Even if attendance is mandatory I enjoyed listening to him and taking notes. Great teacher, interesting subject. You can tell he's passionate and knows what he's talking about. Videos + powerpoints makes for a very interesting class.
love this guy. and other than some of the comments i've seen on here, i haven't spoken to anyone who has had anything negative to say about him either. highly recommended :) he's the best

I actually signed up for this course by accident, thinking it was a Spanish language class. Ended up fully enjoying the class because he has some magic way of using story to teach the material. He uses powerpoint presentations along with videos to support the lectures. Overall a great prof, and very open for discussion during lectures.

I really enjoyed this professor and the course. I thought he was full of interesting knowledge, no need to buy a textbook, and I thought his tests were fair. Even though all texts are on Virtual Campus, I attended all classes because of the interesting info he added as he went over the texts :) Lots of reading though!
This is one of those classes that has ALOT of reading! The exam is all short answer questions.

He's an awkward teacher. At times hard to understand, for ESP1101 you can follow the class and not even attend. Everything is posted on webCT. Less than half of the class is in regular attendance. Don't go to class if you like to eat "noisy or smelly" food and you like to chat a bit.
Look out!  This prof is "very busy and important".  If he gives you 30 seconds of his precious time, take it!  Quite Mr. Burnsy.
